= Sticky Rice <sticky-rice>
== Equipment

- Rice cooker#Fn.rice-cooker

== Ingredients

- 1 cup short-grain white rice
- 1 cup water
- Salt, to taste

*Yields 2 servings.*

== Steps

+ Rinse rice in cold water 4-5 times or until water becomes clear.
+ Place rice in pot, fill with cold water, and let rice soak for 30 minutes.
+ Strain rice.
+ Replace rice into pot alongside preallocated salt & cup of water.
+ Turn rice cooker on. Remember to leave for about 10 minutes after rice cooker goes from cooking mode to warming mode, so as to allow steam to settle.

== Trivia

It frankly baffles me that this recipe works. It seems like rinsing the rice not
just once but effectively twice should get all the loose starches out, which I
_believe_---hang on, is this true?---is what makes sticky rice sticky. It does
work though, which I guess is pretty cool.

Oh, also, "1 cup" is a loose amount here. Make as much as you'd like while
preserving the rice-to-water ratio. The more rice, the lower the chance of
burning, it seems.